<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-31T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/589: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-31T11:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 3:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>51. The Assembly yesterday approved the railway debt settlement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi></signed></closer>
